# CLEAN & NORMALIZE COLUMNS
#    strip currency markers, coerce to numeric
def clean_usd(x):
    if pd.isna(x): return np.nan
    return float(str(x).replace('','').replace(',',''))

for col in ['region_spend_usd','page_spend_usd','state_spend_usd']:
    ads_df[col] = ads_df[col].map(clean_usd)

# 2) FAIRNESSAWARE RANKING SCORE
#    For each region, sort pages by page_spend_usd and compute
#    the fraction of high_pay ads in the topk (k=10).
def ranking_score(df, k=10):
    topk = df.nlargest(k, 'page_spend_usd')
    return (topk.job_type=='high_pay').mean()

ranking_scores = ads_df.groupby('region').apply(ranking_score)
print("\nSample Ranking scores:")
print(ranking_scores.head())

#  Mitigation: Simple Reweighing
#    Well give each ad a weight so that every regions high_pay share = overall mean.
overall = (ads_df.job_type=='high_pay').mean()
weights = []
for region, grp in ads_df.groupby('region'):
    p = (grp.job_type=='high_pay').mean()
    # if p>0, weight_high = overall/p, weight_low = (1-overall)/(1-p)
    wh = overall/p   if p>0   else 0
    wl = (1-overall)/(1-p) if p<1 else 0
    weights.append(pd.Series(np.where(grp.job_type=='high_pay', wh, wl), index=grp.index))
weights = pd.concat(weights).sort_index()
ads_df['reweigh'] = weights

# Apply weights to recompute regional high_pay rates
post_rates = (
    ads_df
      .assign(weighted_high = np.where(ads_df.job_type=='high_pay', ads_df.reweigh, 0))
      .groupby('region')
      [['weighted_high','reweigh']]
      .sum()
)
post_rates['post_rate'] = post_rates.weighted_high / post_rates.reweigh
post_rates = post_rates['post_rate']
print("\nPostmitigation P(high_pay) samples:")
print(post_rates.head())

In[106]:
def inject_bias(ads_df, base_prob=0.3, priv_prob=0.8, unpriv_prob=0.0, show_stats=True):
    df = ads_df.copy()
    df['job_type'] = np.where(np.random.rand(len(df)) < base_prob, 'high_pay', 'low_pay')

    # Inject bias (variable for both regions now)
    df.loc[df.region == unpriv_reg, 'job_type'] = np.where(
        np.random.rand((df.region == unpriv_reg).sum()) < unpriv_prob, 'high_pay', 'low_pay'
    )
    df.loc[df.region == priv_reg, 'job_type'] = np.where(
        np.random.rand((df.region == priv_reg).sum()) < priv_prob, 'high_pay', 'low_pay'
    )

    if show_stats:
        base_rates = df.groupby('region')['job_type'] \
            .apply(lambda s: (s == 'high_pay').mean()).sort_values()

        print(f"\nBias Injection Summary:")
        print(f"- Base assignment probability (all): {base_prob}")
        print(f"- {priv_reg} privileged high-pay rate: {priv_prob}")
        print(f"- {unpriv_reg} unprivileged high-pay rate: {unpriv_prob}\n")

        print("High-pay proportions by region (pre-mitigation):")
        print(base_rates)

    return df
In[109]:
def evaluate_bias_metrics(ads_df, param_grid):
    disparities = []

    for base_p, priv_p in param_grid:
        biased_df = inject_bias(ads_df, base_prob=base_p, priv_prob=priv_p, unpriv_prob=0.1, show_stats=False)

        rates = biased_df.groupby('region')['job_type'].apply(lambda s: (s == 'high_pay').mean())
        disparity = rates[unpriv_reg] / rates[priv_reg]

        disparities.append({
            'base_prob': base_p,
            'priv_prob': priv_p,
            'DI': disparity
        })

    df = pd.DataFrame(disparities)
    pivot = df.pivot(index="base_prob", columns="priv_prob", values="DI")

    pivot.plot(kind='line', marker='o', title='Disparate Impact across parameter sweep')
    plt.ylabel("Disparate Impact (unpriv / priv)")
    plt.xlabel("Base high_pay probability")
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.show()

def evaluate_bias_combinations(ads_df, param_list, unpriv_prob=0.2):
    disparities = []

    for base_p, priv_p in param_list:
        biased_df = inject_bias(ads_df, base_prob=base_p, priv_prob=priv_p, unpriv_prob=unpriv_prob, show_stats=False)

        rates = biased_df.groupby('region')['job_type'].apply(lambda s: (s == 'high_pay').mean())
        disparity = rates[unpriv_reg] / rates[priv_reg]

        disparities.append({
            'setting': f'base={base_p}, priv={priv_p}',
            'DI': disparity
        })

    df = pd.DataFrame(disparities)
    df.set_index('setting', inplace=True)
    df['DI'].plot(kind='barh', color='skyblue')
    plt.title('Disparate Impact for Different Bias Injection Settings')
    plt.xlabel('Disparate Impact (unprivileged / privileged)')
    plt.axvline(1.0, color='green', linestyle='--', label='Fairness Line')
    plt.axvline(0.8, color='red', linestyle='--', label='Bias Threshold')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
